Furthermore, the Azzurri will have former Manchester City man Mario Balotelli leading the attacking line.

Balotelli is capable of everything from the sublime to the ridiculous, and Cahill said: 'That's dangerous isn't it because you never know - will he turn up, will he not?

'He's got potential to stick it into the top corner from 30 yards. He's an unpredictable player but on his day obviously one of the best.

'I played against him a couple of times at City and he's been tough. I played against him another time when he came off after 60, 70 minutes.'He is unpredictable. At times he can be world class. But he's certainly one to watch out for.'

While at times erratic, Balotelli was one of the Premier League's most exciting characters during his time at the Etihad Stadium.

