The Brazil international found starts hard to come by at Chelsea under Jose Mourinho last season, with his exit reflecting well on Cahill and the way he has impressed alongside John Terry in central defence.

'He is a fantastic player, good luck to him,' Cahill added.

'People don't pay that sort of money for average players, they pay that money for the top players and he is in that category.'

